				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No, this is the best method. I looked at the scource of a game (Final Fantasy) and there was one routine to decode 6 digits, one to decode 5 digits, etc... Each one was calling two others routines. The first one does substract the value 10n for each digit and storing them into ram (the routine to decode 6 ditits takes the whole algorithm, but the one who decodes only 5 digits skips one substraction, etc...). The segond routine does remove all unused zeroes (stuff like 000947 will become ___947).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

